{
    "publish_date": "2013-10-21T15:06:04.000Z", 
    "score": 0.0005366596790743643, 
    "video_length": "PT5M4S", 
    "captions": [
        {
            "text": "Have you ever daydreamed\nabout traveling through time,", 
            "dur": "2.572", 
            "start": "6.865"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "perhaps fast forward in the centuries\nand seeing the distant future?", 
            "dur": "3.658", 
            "start": "9.461"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, time travel is possible,", 
            "dur": "2.042", 
            "start": "13.143"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and what&#39;s more, it&#39;s already been done.", 
            "dur": "2.43", 
            "start": "15.209"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Meet Sergei Krikalev,", 
            "dur": "1.271", 
            "start": "17.663"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the greatest time traveler\nin human history.", 
            "dur": "2.768", 
            "start": "18.958"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This Russian cosmonaut holds the record", 
            "dur": "2.012", 
            "start": "21.75"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for the most amount of time\nspent orbiting our planet,", 
            "dur": "2.563", 
            "start": "23.786"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "a total of 803 days,\n9 hours, and 39 minutes.", 
            "dur": "3.688", 
            "start": "26.373"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "During his stay in space,", 
            "dur": "1.317", 
            "start": "31.14"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "he time traveled into his own future", 
            "dur": "1.876", 
            "start": "32.481"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by 0.02 seconds.", 
            "dur": "2.139", 
            "start": "34.381"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Traveling at 17,500 miles an hour,", 
            "dur": "2.51", 
            "start": "37.925"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "he experienced an effect\nknown as time dilation,", 
            "dur": "2.997", 
            "start": "40.459"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and one day the same effect", 
            "dur": "1.606", 
            "start": "43.48"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "might make significant time travel\nto the future commonplace.", 
            "dur": "3.277", 
            "start": "45.11"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "To see why moving faster through space\naffects passage of time,", 
            "dur": "3.278", 
            "start": "49.575"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "we need to go back to the 1880s,", 
            "dur": "2.131", 
            "start": "52.877"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "when two American scientists,", 
            "dur": "1.381", 
            "start": "55.032"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Albert Michelson and Edward Morley,", 
            "dur": "1.905", 
            "start": "56.437"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "were trying to measure the effect\nof the Earth&#39;s movement around the Sun", 
            "dur": "3.412", 
            "start": "58.366"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "on the speed of light.", 
            "dur": "1.294", 
            "start": "61.802"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "When a beam of light was moving\nin the same direction as the Earth,", 
            "dur": "3.147", 
            "start": "63.12"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they expected the light to travel faster.", 
            "dur": "1.972", 
            "start": "66.291"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And when the Earth was moving\nin the opposite direction,", 
            "dur": "2.633", 
            "start": "68.287"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "they expected it to go slower.", 
            "dur": "1.927", 
            "start": "70.944"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But they found something very curious.", 
            "dur": "1.961", 
            "start": "72.895"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "The speed of light remained the same\nno matter what the Earth was doing.", 
            "dur": "3.501", 
            "start": "74.88"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Two decades later,\nAlbert Einstein was thinking", 
            "dur": "2.239", 
            "start": "78.405"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "about the consequences\nof that never-changing speed of light.", 
            "dur": "3.291", 
            "start": "80.668"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And it was his conclusions,", 
            "dur": "1.338", 
            "start": "83.983"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "formulated in the theory\nof special relativity,", 
            "dur": "2.577", 
            "start": "85.345"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that opened the door\ninto the world of time travel.", 
            "dur": "2.818", 
            "start": "87.946"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Imagine a man named Jack,", 
            "dur": "1.727", 
            "start": "90.788"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "standing in the middle\nof a train carriage,", 
            "dur": "2.024", 
            "start": "92.539"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "traveling at a steady speed.", 
            "dur": "1.645", 
            "start": "94.587"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Jack&#39;s bored and starts bouncing\na ball up and down.", 
            "dur": "2.707", 
            "start": "96.256"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "What would Jill, standing on the platform,\nsee through the window", 
            "dur": "3.048", 
            "start": "98.987"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "as the train whistles through?", 
            "dur": "1.546", 
            "start": "102.059"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, between Jack dropping the ball\nand catching it again,", 
            "dur": "2.941", 
            "start": "103.629"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Jill would have seen him move\nslightly further down the track,", 
            "dur": "3.059", 
            "start": "106.594"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "resulting in her seeing the ball\nfollow a triangular path.", 
            "dur": "2.819", 
            "start": "109.676"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This means Jill sees the ball\ntravel further than Jack does", 
            "dur": "2.777", 
            "start": "113.407"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "in the same time period.", 
            "dur": "1.871", 
            "start": "116.208"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And because speed\nis distance divided by time,", 
            "dur": "2.191", 
            "start": "118.103"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Jill actually sees the ball move faster.", 
            "dur": "2.522", 
            "start": "120.318"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But what if Jack&#39;s bouncing ball\nis replaced with two mirrors", 
            "dur": "2.882", 
            "start": "123.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "which bounce a beam of light between them?", 
            "dur": "2.092", 
            "start": "126.736"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Jack still sees the beam dropping down", 
            "dur": "2.233", 
            "start": "128.852"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "and Jill still sees the light beam\ntravel a longer distance,", 
            "dur": "3.177", 
            "start": "131.109"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "except this time Jack and Jill\ncannot disagree on the speed", 
            "dur": "3.115", 
            "start": "134.31"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "because the speed of light\nremains the same no matter what.", 
            "dur": "3.15", 
            "start": "137.449"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "And if the speed is the same\nwhile the distance is different,", 
            "dur": "2.929", 
            "start": "141.535"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "this means the time taken\nwill be different as well.", 
            "dur": "2.51", 
            "start": "144.488"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Thus, time must tick at different rates\nfor people moving relative to each other.", 
            "dur": "4.252", 
            "start": "147.911"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Imagine that Jack and Jill\nhave highly accurate watches", 
            "dur": "2.619", 
            "start": "152.187"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that they synchronize\nbefore Jack boards the train.", 
            "dur": "3.191", 
            "start": "154.83"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "During the experiment,\nJack and Jill would each see", 
            "dur": "2.381", 
            "start": "158.045"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "their own watch ticking normally.", 
            "dur": "1.62", 
            "start": "160.45"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But if they meet up again later\nto compare watches,", 
            "dur": "3.084", 
            "start": "163.053"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "less time would have\nelapsed on Jack&#39;s watch,", 
            "dur": "2.166", 
            "start": "166.161"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "balancing the fact that Jill saw\nthe light move further.", 
            "dur": "3.206", 
            "start": "168.351"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "This idea may sound crazy,", 
            "dur": "1.657", 
            "start": "172.394"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "but like any good scientific theory,", 
            "dur": "2.029", 
            "start": "174.075"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it can be tested.", 
            "dur": "1", 
            "start": "176.128"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In the 1970s, scientists boarded a plane", 
            "dur": "2.385", 
            "start": "178.051"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "with some super-accurate atomic clocks", 
            "dur": "2.061", 
            "start": "180.46"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "that were synchronized\nwith some others left on the ground.", 
            "dur": "2.771", 
            "start": "182.545"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "After the plane had\nflown around the world,", 
            "dur": "2.047", 
            "start": "186.188"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the clocks on board\nshowed a different time", 
            "dur": "2.001", 
            "start": "188.259"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "from those left behind.", 
            "dur": "1.294", 
            "start": "190.284"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Of course, at the speed\nof trains and planes,", 
            "dur": "2.205", 
            "start": "192.522"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "the effect is minuscule.", 
            "dur": "1.45", 
            "start": "194.751"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But the faster you go,\nthe more time dilates.", 
            "dur": "2.333", 
            "start": "196.225"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "For astronauts orbiting\nthe Earth for 800 days,", 
            "dur": "2.57", 
            "start": "198.582"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "it starts to add up.", 
            "dur": "1.56", 
            "start": "201.176"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But what affects humans\nalso affects machines.", 
            "dur": "2.783", 
            "start": "202.76"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Satellites of the global\npositioning system", 
            "dur": "2.151", 
            "start": "205.567"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "are also hurdling around the Earth", 
            "dur": "1.643", 
            "start": "207.742"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "at thousands of miles an hour.", 
            "dur": "1.483", 
            "start": "209.409"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, time dilation kicks in here, too.", 
            "dur": "2.323", 
            "start": "210.916"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "In fact, their speed causes\nthe atomic clocks on board", 
            "dur": "2.688", 
            "start": "214.291"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to disagree with clocks on the ground", 
            "dur": "1.762", 
            "start": "217.003"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by seven millionths of a second daily.", 
            "dur": "2.018", 
            "start": "218.789"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Left uncorrected,", 
            "dur": "1.435", 
            "start": "220.831"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "this would cause GPS to lose accuracy", 
            "dur": "1.83", 
            "start": "222.29"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "by a few kilometers each day.", 
            "dur": "1.847", 
            "start": "224.144"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "So, what does all this have\nto do with time travel", 
            "dur": "2.381", 
            "start": "227.589"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to the far, distant future?", 
            "dur": "1.767", 
            "start": "229.994"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Well, the faster you go,\nthe greater the effect of time dilation.", 
            "dur": "3.353", 
            "start": "231.785"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "If you could travel really close", 
            "dur": "1.524", 
            "start": "235.162"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to the speed of light, say 99.9999%,", 
            "dur": "4.059", 
            "start": "236.71"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "on a round-trip through space", 
            "dur": "1.381", 
            "start": "240.793"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "for what seemed to you like ten years,", 
            "dur": "2.501", 
            "start": "242.198"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "you&#39;d actually return to Earth", 
            "dur": "1.429", 
            "start": "244.723"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "around the year 9000.", 
            "dur": "2.228", 
            "start": "246.176"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Who knows what you&#39;d see\nwhen you returned?!", 
            "dur": "2.123", 
            "start": "248.428"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "Humanity merged with machines,", 
            "dur": "1.647", 
            "start": "250.575"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "extinct due to climate change\nor asteroid impact,", 
            "dur": "3.063", 
            "start": "252.246"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "or inhabiting a permanent colony on Mars.", 
            "dur": "2.388", 
            "start": "255.333"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But the trouble is,", 
            "dur": "1.036", 
            "start": "258.952"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "getting heavy things like people,\nnot to mention space ships,", 
            "dur": "2.88", 
            "start": "260.012"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "up to such speeds requires\nunimaginable amounts of energy.", 
            "dur": "3.688", 
            "start": "262.916"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "It already takes enormous\nparticle accelerators", 
            "dur": "2.718", 
            "start": "266.628"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "like the Large Hadron Collider", 
            "dur": "1.523", 
            "start": "269.37"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "to accelerate tiny subatomic particles\nto close to light speed.", 
            "dur": "3.658", 
            "start": "270.917"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "But one day, if we can develop the tools\nto accelerate ourselves to similar speeds,", 
            "dur": "4.006", 
            "start": "275.483"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "then we may regularly send time travelers", 
            "dur": "1.953", 
            "start": "279.513"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "into the future,", 
            "dur": "1.039", 
            "start": "281.49"
        }, 
        {
            "text": "bringing with them tales\nof a long, forgotten past.", 
            "dur": "2.528", 
            "start": "282.553"
        }
    ], 
